Colour pattern . Semitransparent with reddish chromatophores forming more or less distinct bands, two on the carapace and six on the abdomen; scattered red chromatophores also on antennular peduncles, chelipeds, walking legs and tail fan; eggs / embryos dark brown-red (
Figs. 5–7
).

Distribution . Presently known only from the type locality in French Polynesia (see
Fig. 11
).
